1
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:05,360
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:07,280
Cairo

3
00:00:10,880 --> 00:00:16,400
Monica noticed the gift shop, because of the 
beautiful colours round its door and window.  

4
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:24,320
She walked through its entrance which had a sign 
above it. On the sign, the word Cairo was written  

5
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:30,240
in bright yellow, orange and green colours, 
with small black figures dancing beside it.

6
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:41,600
Inside, it was just as colourful. Large animals 
made of paper, painted in very bright colours,  

7
00:00:41,600 --> 00:00:50,080
hung from the ceiling. The floor had a 
yellow-brown sand colour to it, and the shelves  

8
00:00:50,080 --> 00:00:57,840
held vases, plates, boxes, musical instruments 
and jewellery Monica had never seen before.

9
00:00:58,480 --> 00:01:02,560
No one seemed to be in the shop; not a salesperson  

10
00:01:02,560 --> 00:01:08,160
or a customer. Light Arab music came 
from a stereo Monica could not see,  

11
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:13,520
but she moved with its sound as she looked 
at all the wonderful objects in the shop.  

12
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:20,000
She saw a blue stone on a gold 
necklace which looked interesting.  

13
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:27,200
Drawn in the centre of the stone there was 
something which looked like a large round beetle,  

14
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:31,360
with thin legs and thick 
antennae coming from its head.

15
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:34,480
"It's an Egyptian scarab."

16
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:42,800
The woman's voice surprised, then frightened 
Monica. She almost dropped the necklace.

17
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:47,520
"I'm sorry I didn't know anyone was here."

18
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:53,840
"It's okay, my dear. I knew 
you would be here. Come. Come."

19
00:01:55,120 --> 00:02:00,320
The woman took Monica's arm and led her 
behind the sales counter to a small area  

20
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:02,480
where there was a round table and two chairs.  

21
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:09,840
It was dark because cloth the colour of sand, with 
dark patterns, hung from the walls and ceilings.  

22
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:16,880
It was almost closed off from the rest of 
the shop by a curtain, so most of the light  

23
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:24,000
came from a few candles set around the room. It 
was like a small cave from somewhere far away.

24
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:30,880
"Sit. I've made us some tea, 
black tea; the tea of judgement."

25
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,240
"Judgement?"

26
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:37,280
"Yes. The tea leaves tell us 
about a person's entire life.  

27
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:42,560
Some of us have done things we wish we 
hadn't. Some of us haven't done things  

28
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:49,920
we wish we had. Some of us are messengers. 
Some of us are waiting for the message."

29
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:53,600
The woman wore a piece of red 
cloth tied around her head.  

30
00:02:54,960 --> 00:03:01,760
It hid the colour of her hair. Her eyes 
were large and dark. They became larger  

31
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:09,360
when she talked. As Monica sat at the table, she 
realised she still had the necklace in her hand.

32
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:15,520
"This stone is quite beautiful. 
I've never seen anything like it."

33
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:20,800
"It is lapis lazuli, the ancient blue 
stone used to make statues for the gods.  

34
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:27,200
It was found in rock, and the rock had to be 
burned and broken to get the lapis lazuli out.  

35
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,000
That shows you how strong it is."

36
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:33,360
"Well, I'm sure it's too expensive for me..."

37
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,680
As Monica was about to put 
the necklace on the table,  

38
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:42,480
the woman closed her hand around 
Monica's, to keep the stone there.

39
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,800
"Don't let it go, now that you have 
it. It may help you see things you  

40
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,240
never thought were possible."

41
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,280
"But... I..."

42
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:56,880
The woman put her finger on Monica's 
lips so that she couldn't talk.

43
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:03,360
"Sit and listen and I will tell 
you the story of the blue scarab."

44
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:10,640
Monica held the necklace in her hand while 
the woman spoke. Whether it was the heat of  

45
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:15,840
the room, the tea, or the woman's soft 
voice, Monica began to fall asleep.

46
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:26,720
"The scarab is the sacred beetle of the sun 
god, the most important of all the gods as it  

47
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:33,680
makes people see things in a different way. It is 
given to a different person every hundred years.  

48
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:41,520
The person is chosen by the sun god to act as a 
messenger for the dead. They see and understand  

49
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:47,360
things on earth that help the gods decide 
whether the dead have lived good or bad lives.  

50
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:53,520
Those who wear it are sometimes frightened 
because they are able to see the dead  

51
00:04:53,520 --> 00:05:01,200
living again. But they must keep the scarab, 
as the judgement of so many depends on them."

52
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:08,960
Monica heard the woman's words as she slept. 
She saw herself living thousands of years ago,  

53
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:17,120
wearing the scarab. People were touching her 
hand as she passed them. She was smiling and  

54
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:23,840
she felt very peaceful. When she opened her 
eyes, she looked at the woman talking to her.

55
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,160
"It looks good on you."

56
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:37,840
Monica touched the necklace with her 
fingers. It was now round her neck.
 
 
 

57
00:05:50,400 --> 00:06:04,800
CHAPTER TWO

58
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:45,840
Herbie

59
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:56,800
Monica's car had a broken headlight. As she drove 
to a garage to have it fixed, the sun came down  

60
00:10:56,800 --> 00:11:01,280
through the trees along the road, making 
everything seem more alive than usual.

61
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:07,040
There was an old man cleaning 
the ground in front of the garage  

62
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:14,240
when Monica parked her car. He had 
his back to her, so she called to him:

63
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,720
"Excuse me. Do you work here?"

64
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,920
The man did not turn round.

65
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,840
"Excuse me."

66
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,520
Monica put her hand on the man's shoulder.  

67
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:33,360
He turned quickly and Monica saw 
her father's face. Frightened,  

68
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:39,200
she put her hands over her mouth. Her father had 
died five years earlier when she was eighteen.

69
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:44,080
"Dad! Is that you?" 

70
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:49,040
Tears came to her eyes and her hands shook.  

71
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:55,840
The man moved his fingers to his mouth and 
ears to show her he could not speak or hear.

72
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,440
"Hello there!"

73
00:11:58,640 --> 00:12:03,760
It was the voice of a young man Monica knew 
from the university. She had forgotten his name.

74
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:08,320
"It's Owen, remember? We 
met at a party last winter."

75
00:12:09,280 --> 00:12:12,160
"Oh, er yes! I'm Monica."

76
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:16,480
"I suppose you' ve met Herbie. He just 
started working here this morning."

77
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:21,520
Monica wouldn't look at the man, 
afraid of what she would see.  

78
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:28,640
He was talking to Owen in sign language. Owen 
spoke as he made the signs with his fingers.

79
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:38,080
"Of course you can. I told you, Mr Burns 
lets us take our lunch whenever we want.  

80
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:43,120
As long as you've finished your 
work. Okay, you're welcome."

81
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:51,840
Herbie walked away. Suddenly, 
Owen noticed Monica's necklace.

82
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,440
"Is that a blue scarab you're wearing?"

83
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:58,560
"Yes, a woman at a shop gave it to me. 
She wouldn't take any money for it."

84
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:03,520
"It was found in a chest believed to be the 
chest of Osiris, an ancient Egyptian god.  

85
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:08,160
I read about it in my class on 
ancient Egypt. I study archaeology."

86
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:10,880
"I think I saw you leaving 
that class once. I had an  

87
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,360
economics class right after it in the same room."

88
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:16,640
"It's a small world. So, 
what's wrong with your car?"

89
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:17,680
"It needs a new headlight."

90
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,840
"Oh, that's no problem. I 
can fix that in ten minutes.  

91
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:24,000
Why don't you go sit in the office? While 
you wait, Mr Burns will write out your bill."

92
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:35,120
In the office next to the garage, Mr Burns sat 
behind his desk smoking a cigar. He was a short,  

93
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:39,920
bald man, but Monica didn't know how 
short until he stood up to shake her hand.

94
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,720
"Nathan Burns. Pleased to meet you."

95
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:48,320
"Monica Halloway. Owen's fixing my headlight. 
Er, he said you'd write up the papers."

96
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:52,320
"Certainly I will. You just have a seat 
there. I'll take care of it in two minutes."

97
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:57,920
Monica looked out of the office 
window at Owen working on her car.  

98
00:13:59,040 --> 00:14:02,560
His thin, young face began to look old and tired.

99
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:06,880
It was as if she was looking 
at a completely different man  

100
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:12,480
and it frightened her. Mr Burn's 
voice stopped her thinking.

101
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,880
"How do you spell, Halloway, with two Ls or one?"

102
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:22,880
"What? Oh, two. H, A, double L, O, W, A, Y."

103
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:30,960
Monica went outside to see Owen as he finished his 
work on her car. He looked like he usually did,  

104
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:36,720
and Monica forgot about what she thought 
she had seen before. She shook his hand.

105
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,040
"Thank you very much for your help."

106
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:41,120
"Anytime. It was nice to see you again."

107
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:46,720
When Owen walked away, Monica saw Herbie 
sitting on a chair by the garage door.  

108
00:14:47,760 --> 00:14:51,680
He was eating a sandwich. She 
saw something on his right arm.  

109
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:56,400
It was a purple birthmark, 
the same kind her father had.

110
00:14:57,280 --> 00:15:00,320
"It is you. I knew it!"

111
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:05,360
She took a few steps towards 
Herbie, but she frightened him.  

112
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:25,840
He got up and went into the garage. When she 
followed him inside, she saw that he had gone.
 
 
 

113
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:36,160
CHAPTER THREE

114
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:39,840
Tops

115
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:41,760
"Look. If you don't stop this, you'll get 
yourself into trouble. It was a mistake.  

116
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:43,520
You saw something which wasn't there,"

117
00:17:44,960 --> 00:17:46,960
Yvonne was able to make Monica relax.  

118
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,760
They ordered their pizza and began 
to talk about other things when

119
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,440
Monica saw Owen across the room.

120
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:59,840
"Now don't tell me I don't see him. 
That's the guy who fixed my car."

121
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:07,120
Owen saw them looking over at him, and he 
waved hello. He walked over and sat with them.

122
00:18:08,320 --> 00:18:09,680
"I'm glad I found you."

123
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,520
"Owen, this is Yvonne."

124
00:18:11,520 --> 00:18:15,040
"Pleased to meet you. Look, I've 
read more about your blue scarab."

125
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:18,880
"Wait a minute... wait a minute! I've 
just finished telling her that there  

126
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:22,640
is no such thing as ghosts or sun gods 
or whatever else you want to tell her."

127
00:18:22,640 --> 00:18:24,240
"Yvonne, let him finish."

128
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:30,320
"The ancient Egyptians believed that Osiris, the 
sun god's helper, used that stone so that people  

129
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:34,880
on earth could help those who had died. They 
thought dead people had to go through a trial.  

130
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:39,200
In that trial, they had to show that 
the good things they had done on earth  

131
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:43,600
were greater than the bad things. Their actions 
could help the living improve themselves by  

132
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:48,320
teaching them something. If the living learn 
something valuable from the life of someone else,  

133
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:51,680
who is now dead, they can continue 
living their lives in a better way.  

134
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:57,040
This is good for the living but also for 
the dead. The gods will see that the dead  

135
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:01,120
had lived good lives since they continue 
influencing the living in a positive way."

136
00:19:02,160 --> 00:19:04,480
"Owen, that was thousands of years ago!"

137
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:06,000
"Wait a minute, Yvonne.  

138
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:12,320
Let's just try to understand this. Do you think 
I could have seen a dead person alive again?"

139
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:16,080
"I don't know about that, but I know 
someone who does, and he'd like to meet you.  

140
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:21,040
His name is Professor Lloyd. He taught that 
class on ancient Egypt I told you about.  

141
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,080
Would you like to talk to him?"

142
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:23,200
"Why not?"

143
00:19:23,760 --> 00:19:24,640
"This is mad!"

144
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:30,640
Monica was silent for a few minutes, 
because she was thinking of her father.  

145
00:19:32,160 --> 00:19:33,920
She finally asked Owen about Herbie.

146
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:40,160
"Who's that old man who is working at 
the garage? What's his name, Herbie?"

147
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:51,840
"Yeah, Herbie. Strange, but right after you left, 
we couldn't find him. He never came back."
 
 
 

148
00:20:02,560 --> 00:20:05,920
CHAPTER FOUR

149
00:20:05,920 --> 00:20:06,960
Professor Lloyd

150
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:21,760
When Owen and Monica knocked on Professor 
Lloyd's door, they heard a cat miaowing inside.  

151
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,920
They heard Professor Lloyd's 
footsteps coming toward the door,  

152
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,600
then they saw him: a tall 
well-built man with glasses.  

153
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:39,840
He had straight, grey-white hair and a soft, 
kind face. He welcomed them with a large smile.

154
00:20:40,400 --> 00:20:41,280
"You must be Monica."

155
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:45,360
"Hello Professor Lloyd. It's 
a pleasure to meet you."

156
00:20:45,360 --> 00:20:46,320
"The pleasure is mine.  

157
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:51,760
From what Owen tells me, you have something 
which may be more powerful than we know."

158
00:20:53,440 --> 00:21:00,240
Professor Lloyd's flat was filled with books and 
cats. Each wall was covered with shelves of books,  

159
00:21:00,240 --> 00:21:04,880
and there were cats of every different colour 
sitting on tables, walking across the floor,  

160
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:10,640
or rubbing themselves against Monica's legs. 
Monica picked up a black one with white paws.

161
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:14,080
"I love your cats, Professor."

162
00:21:14,640 --> 00:21:18,560
"The Kauri Indians of southern Peru 
believe the cat spirit controls our lives.  

163
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:21,840
They probably know my cats and my life."

164
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:28,960
Professor Lloyd laughed loudly. He picked 
up two of the cats as they walked to the  

165
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:33,920
middle of the room where a bright light hung 
over a square white table with four chairs.

166
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:40,880
They sat at the table, and the professor 
asked to see the blue scarab. He put a round,  

167
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:46,320
one-inch eyepiece with black glass over his 
left eye, and he studied the back of the stone.

168
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:51,040
"Ah, yes. Here are the markings."

169
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:58,160
The professor was quiet. He took 
the eyepiece away from his eye  

170
00:21:58,160 --> 00:22:02,320
and looked at Monica. Owen was worried.

171
00:22:03,680 --> 00:22:04,720
"What is it Professor?"

172
00:22:05,600 --> 00:22:08,800
"It seems that Monica has been 
chosen as a messenger for the gods."

173
00:22:09,360 --> 00:22:13,440
"Gods! Professor, you don't really 
believe in the gods, do you?"

174
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:17,440
"What I mean is that this stone is 
exactly like the one in ancient mythology.  

175
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:21,200
The myth says that certain 
people are chosen to wear it."

176
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:24,880
"That's what the woman said who gave it to me."

177
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,360
"Professor, what are the markings?"

178
00:22:28,480 --> 00:22:30,720
The Professor held the stone up to the light.

179
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:37,680
"You can't see it clearly without the eyepiece, 
but this marking here is the teeth of a dog.  

180
00:22:38,640 --> 00:22:45,120
The dog watches over the dead. And here is the 
wing of a hawk. The hawk cries for the revenge  

181
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:51,200
of the dead. But here is the sign connecting 
all the others - the round horn of the ram.  

182
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:58,400
This represents the power of water. It can 
give life to the dead. The scarab on the front,  

183
00:22:58,400 --> 00:23:03,680
which represents the sun, acts together with water 
to bring peace to both the living and the dead."

184
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:05,840
"How do you know all this?"

185
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:11,120
"It is written in ancient Egyptian tombs, but 
there is another way to see if we are right."

186
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:12,160
"What's that?"

187
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:21,840
"We can test the stone to see 
what kind of power it has."
 
 
 

188
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:42,960
CHAPTER FIVE

189
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:49,840
Professor Lloyd's Back Room

190
00:23:52,560 --> 00:23:56,640
Professor Lloyd took Owen and 
Monica to the back room of his flat,  

191
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:59,120
where all the walls were 
covered with black curtains.  

192
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:05,680
In the centre of the room, there was a round, 
wooden table with strange black markings on it.  

193
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:10,800
In the centre, there was a circle with 
the drawing of an eye in the middle of it.  

194
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:16,720
Four spears, like rays of sunlight, went from 
the central circle to the edge of the table,  

195
00:24:17,440 --> 00:24:22,960
dividing the table into four 
equal parts. There was another  

196
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:27,120
thin circle of numbers and letters 
that went round the edge of the table.  

197
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:35,520
Between the central circle and the circle at the 
edge of the table there were four equal spaces. In  

198
00:24:35,520 --> 00:24:45,840
each there was a picture: one of a fish, one of a 
snake, one of the moon, and one of a lotus flower.

199
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:53,120
Professor Lloyd lit candles in the room as Owen 
and Monica sat at the table. The professor put  

200
00:24:53,120 --> 00:25:00,000
on a tall black hat with a flat top, and a 
long black robe. He was the first to speak.

201
00:25:01,360 --> 00:25:04,080
"We are going to try to call 
people back from the dead.  

202
00:25:05,040 --> 00:25:09,520
If the stone has the power the myth says 
it does, we may hear voices we know."

203
00:25:11,280 --> 00:25:16,640
The professor put the scarab over the eye in the 
centre of the table, with the beetle facing up.

204
00:25:18,240 --> 00:25:21,280
"Now, we must all hold hands and close our eyes.  

205
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:26,960
Do not break the circle by letting go of the 
hand of the person who is sitting next to you,  

206
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:33,440
or the ceremony will end. Relax, 
breathe slowly, and do not speak."

207
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:42,000
They were all very quiet. They 
heard a soft whistling sound.

208
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:48,640
It became louder, like the sound of the wind. 
The room became cold and all the candles were  

